Template: blockhost-broker/existing-contract
Type: string
Description: BrokerRequests contract address
 Enter the address of your BrokerRequests contract (if you have one).
 .
 Leave blank to configure later. You can deploy contracts separately
 using: blockhost-broker deploy-contracts
 .
 Format: 0x followed by 40 hexadecimal characters

Template: blockhost-broker/ipv6-interface
Type: select
Choices: ${INTERFACES}
Description: IPv6 interface selection
 Select the IPv6 interface to use for the broker.
 .
 The broker will allocate prefixes from this interface's address range.

Template: blockhost-broker/ipv6-prefix
Type: string
Description: Upstream IPv6 prefix
 Enter the upstream IPv6 prefix for allocations.
 .
 This is the prefix range from which client allocations will be made.
 .
 Format: address/prefix_length (e.g., 2001:db8::/48)

Template: blockhost-broker/allocation-size
Type: select
Choices: 64, 112, 120, 124, 128
Default: 64
Description: Allocation size (prefix length)
 Select the prefix length for client allocations.
 .
  /64: Standard (18 quintillion addresses per host)
  /112: Medium (65,536 addresses per host)
  /120: Small (256 addresses per host)
  /124: Minimal (16 addresses per host)
  /128: Single address per host

Template: blockhost-broker/broker-ipv6
Type: string
Description: Broker IPv6 address
 Enter the broker's own IPv6 address.
 .
 This should be an address within your upstream prefix that the broker
 will use for its own communication.
 .
 Example: 2001:db8::1

Template: blockhost-broker/wg-interface
Type: string
Default: wg-broker
Description: WireGuard interface name
 Enter the name for the WireGuard interface.

Template: blockhost-broker/wg-port
Type: string
Default: 51820
Description: WireGuard listen port
 Enter the UDP port for WireGuard to listen on.

Template: blockhost-broker/wg-endpoint
Type: string
Description: Public endpoint (hostname:port)
 Enter the public hostname or IP address and port that clients
 will use to connect to this broker.
 .
 Format: hostname:port or ip:port
 Example: broker.example.com:51820

Template: blockhost-broker/upstream-interface
Type: string
Description: Upstream network interface for NDP proxy
 Enter the upstream network interface name for NDP proxy.
 .
 This is the interface connected to your IPv6 provider (e.g., sit1 for a
 SIT tunnel, he-ipv6 for Hurricane Electric, or eth0 for native IPv6).
 .
 NDP proxy entries will be added on this interface so that your provider
 can route traffic to allocated client addresses.
 .
 Leave blank to skip NDP proxy configuration.
